RUSTENBURG, September 20 – Deputy President David Mabuza is expected to launch the North West chapter of the Human Resource Development Council (HRDC)  in Rustenburg on Thursday. Mabuza is the chairperson of the HRDC which was launched in 2010 and mobilises stakeholders behind the country’s Human Resource Development Strategy towards 2030. The strategy aims to develop skills that serve the needs of the economy and support the national objectives of radical economic transformation towards inclusive growth. The North West HRDC will consist of members from organised labour, the government, business, civil society and academics. The launch coincides with a two day North West provincial skills development lekgotla (meeting) aimed at deepening skills development efforts and responds to the needs of the province’s economy. – African News Agency (ANA)